[2026-03-13T18:27:02Z] [llm] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01R6FyHX8ezBGpk4fQZXf4qj","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now let me provide a comprehensive summary of my findings:\n\n## Summary of Cloche `list` Command Implementation\n\nBased on my thorough exploration of the codebase, here's a complete analysis of the `cloche list` command and related components:\n\n### 1. **CLI Command Implementation**\n**File:** `/workspace/cmd/cloche/main.go` (lines 241-295)\n\nThe `cmdList` function:\n- Parses the `--all` flag from command-line arguments\n- Creates a `ListRunsRequest` with either:\n  - `All: true` to show all runs across all projects (when `--all` is specified)\n  - `ProjectDir: <current-working-directory>` to show runs for the current project only (default behavior)\n- Default behavior when neither flag is set: filters to current project\n- When `--all` is NOT set and no `ProjectDir` is specified: shows last 1 hour of runs\n- Formats output showing: run ID, workflow name, state, type (host/container), title, container ID, and error message\n\n**Output Format (line 275):**\n```\n<run-id>  <workflow-name (20 chars)>  <state (10 chars)>  <type (9 chars)>  [title]  [container-id]  [error-message]\n```\n\n### 2. **gRPC Proto Definition**\n**File:** `/workspace/api/proto/cloche/v1/cloche.proto` (lines 90-109)\n\n**Request Message (`ListRunsRequest`):**\n```protobuf\nmessage ListRunsRequest {\n  bool all = 1;           // Show all runs across projects\n  string project_dir = 2; // Filter by project directory\n}\n```\n\n**Response Message (`ListRunsResponse`):**\n```protobuf\nmessage ListRunsResponse {\n  repeated RunSummary runs = 1;\n}\n```\n\n**RunSummary Fields:**\n- `run_id` - Unique run identifier\n- `workflow_name` - Name of the workflow\n- `state` - Current state (pending/running/succeeded/failed/cancelled)\n- `started_at` - When the run started\n- `error_message` - Error details (if failed)\n- `container_id` - Docker container ID\n- `title` - Human-readable run title\n- `is_host` - Boolean: true for host workflow runs\n- `project_dir` - Project directory path\n\n### 3. **RunStore Interface**\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/ports/store.go` (lines 10-19)\n\nCore interface methods for listing runs:\n```go\ntype RunStore interface {\n  ListRuns(ctx context.Context, since time.Time) ([]*domain.Run, error)\n  ListRunsByProject(ctx context.Context, projectDir string, since time.Time) ([]*domain.Run, error)\n  ListProjects(ctx context.Context) ([]string, error)\n  ListChildRuns(ctx context.Context, parentRunID string) ([]*domain.Run, error)\n  // ... other methods\n}\n```\n\n### 4. **SQLite Store Implementation**\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/sqlite/store.go`\n\n#### `ListRuns()` (lines 194-210):\n- If `since` is zero (empty): returns all runs with no time filter\n- Otherwise: filters to runs started after `since` timestamp\n- **Sorting:** Prioritizes running runs first, then orders by `started_at DESC`\n- SQL uses: `CASE WHEN state = 'running' THEN 0 ELSE 1 END, started_at DESC`\n\n#### `ListRunsByProject()` (lines 225-242):\n- Filters by `projectDir` and optionally by `since` timestamp\n- Same sorting as `ListRuns()`\n- Returns only runs matching the project directory\n\n#### `ListProjects()` (lines 244-261):\n- Returns distinct project directories across all runs\n- Excludes empty project directories\n\n#### `ListChildRuns()` (lines 263-272):\n- Lists runs that are children of a parent run (for host orchestration)\n- Ordered by `started_at ASC`\n\n#### `ListRunsSince()` (lines 395-416):\n- Evolution-specific method for listing runs since a trigger run\n- Used for intelligent workflow evolution\n\n### 5. **Domain Types**\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/domain/run.go`\n\n**RunState Constants (lines 8-16):**\n```go\ntype RunState string\n\nconst (\n  RunStatePending   RunState = \"pending\"\n  RunStateRunning   RunState = \"running\"\n  RunStateSucceeded RunState = \"succeeded\"\n  RunStateFailed    RunState = \"failed\"\n  RunStateCancelled RunState = \"cancelled\"\n)\n```\n\n**Run Struct (lines 31-48):**\n```go\ntype Run struct {\n  ID             string\n  WorkflowName   string\n  State          RunState\n  ActiveSteps    []string\n  StepExecutions []*StepExecution\n  StartedAt      time.Time\n  CompletedAt    time.Time\n  ProjectDir     string\n  ErrorMessage   string\n  ContainerID    string\n  BaseSHA        string\n  ContainerKept  bool\n  Title          string\n  IsHost         bool\n  ParentRunID    string\n  TaskID         string\n}\n```\n\n### 6. **gRPC Server Implementation**\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go` (lines 387-417)\n\nThe `ListRuns()` RPC handler:\n1. Checks request flags:\n   - If `ProjectDir` is set: calls `store.ListRunsByProject(ctx, projectDir, time.Time{})` (no time filter)\n   - Else if `All` is true: calls `store.ListRuns(ctx, time.Time{})` (no time filter)\n   - Else: calls `store.ListRuns(ctx, now.Add(-1*time.Hour))` (last 1 hour only)\n2. Converts domain `Run` objects to proto `RunSummary` messages\n3. Returns `ListRunsResponse` with populated runs list\n\n### 7. **Help Documentation**\n**File:** `/workspace/cmd/cloche/help.go` (lines 158-175)\n\n```\ncloche list — List workflow runs\n\nShows all runs for the current project, or all runs across all projects\nwith --all.\n\nUsage:\n  cloche list [--all]\n\nFlags:\n  --all    Show runs from all projects (default: current project only).\n\nOutput columns: run ID, workflow name, state, type (host/container),\ntitle, container ID, and error message (if any).\n```\n\n### 8. **SQLite Schema**\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/sqlite/store.go` (lines 46-89)\n\nRelevant tables:\n```sql\nCREATE TABLE runs (\n  id TEXT PRIMARY KEY,\n  workflow_name TEXT NOT NULL,\n  state TEXT NOT NULL,\n  active_steps TEXT,\n  started_at TEXT,\n  completed_at TEXT,\n  project_dir TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT '',\n  error_message TEXT,\n  container_id TEXT,\n  base_sha TEXT,\n  container_kept INTEGER NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,\n  title TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT '',\n  is_host INTEGER NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,\n  parent_run_id TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT '',\n  task_id TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT ''\n);\n```\n\n### 9. **Query Patterns & Filtering**\n\n**Current Filtering Capabilities:**\n1. **Project-based filtering** - Filter by `project_dir`\n2. **Global filtering** - Show all runs across all projects with `--all`\n3. **Time-based filtering** - Automatic 1-hour window when showing current project runs\n4. **State-based sorting** - Running runs prioritized in results\n5. **Temporal sorting** - Runs ordered by `started_at DESC` (newest first)\n\n**NOT YET IMPLEMENTED:**\n- State filtering (e.g., `--state running`, `--state failed`)\n- Workflow name filtering (e.g., `--workflow develop`)\n- Time range filtering (e.g., `--since 1h`, `--until 2h ago`)\n- Full-text search on titles/error messages\n- Limit/offset pagination\n- Detailed format options (JSON, CSV, verbose)\n\n### 10. **Existing Tests**\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server_test.go` (lines 26-72)\n\n- `TestServer_ListRuns_Empty()` - Empty list handling\n- `TestServer_ListRuns_FilterByProject()` - Project filtering validation\n\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/sqlite/store_test.go`\n\n- `TestListRunsByProject()` - Project filtering tests\n- `TestListRunsSortRunningFirst()` - Sorting order verification\n- Multiple integration tests validating list output\n\n### Key Files Summary\n| File Path | Purpose |\n|-----------|---------|\n| `/workspace/cmd/cloche/main.go` | CLI entry point (lines 241-295) |\n| `/workspace/cmd/cloche/help.go` | Help text documentation |\n| `/workspace/api/proto/cloche/v1/cloche.proto` | gRPC proto definitions |\n| `/workspace/internal/ports/store.go` | Store interface definitions |\n| `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go` | gRPC server implementation (lines 387-417) |\n| `/workspace/internal/adapters/sqlite/store.go` | SQLite implementations (lines 194-242) |\n| `/workspace/internal/domain/run.go` | Domain types and constants |\n| `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server_test.go` | gRPC tests (lines 26-72) |\n| `/workspace/internal/adapters/sqlite/store_test.go` | Store tests |\n\nThis comprehensive exploration reveals a clean, layered architecture with clear separation between CLI, gRPC transport, business logic, and data storage layers, all using hexagonal/port-adapter patterns."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a72affc051852427f (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 67070\ntool_uses: 24\nduration_ms: 47092</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c0b250b2-f9c5-4d6e-a2b5-21933ebd9c8c","uuid":"425f2b35-8fb5-4e2b-8a23-efec39d93bde","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore the codebase thoroughly to understand:\n1. The `cloche list` CLI command implementation - find all relevant files\n2. The run store interface and implementations (how runs are listed/filtered)\n3. The domain types for Run, RunState, etc.\n4. The gRPC service definitions (proto files) for listing runs\n5. Any existing filter/query patterns in the codebase\n\nSearch for: list command, ListRuns, RunStore, run state types, proto files, and any existing filtering patterns. Be very thorough.","agentId":"a72affc051852427f","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now let me provide a comprehensive summary of my findings:\n\n## Summary of Cloche `list` Command Implementation\n\nBased on my thorough exploration of the codebase, here's a complete analysis of the `cloche list` command and related components:\n\n### 1. **CLI Command Implementation**\n**File:** `/workspace/cmd/cloche/main.go` (lines 241-295)\n\nThe `cmdList` function:\n- Parses the `--all` flag from command-line arguments\n- Creates a `ListRunsRequest` with either:\n  - `All: true` to show all runs across all projects (when `--all` is specified)\n  - `ProjectDir: <current-working-directory>` to sh