[2026-03-13T18:28:28Z] [llm] {"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_01Do1EYA12kMCmJLP7uSTuAH","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_016xZNteQag7KYj8vHVTuy82","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"/workspace/docs/plans/2026-02-20-cloche-system-design.md"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":7,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2680,"cache_read_input_tokens":14066,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":2680,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_014nB1uYcqdGQDnmCdayJAtm","session_id":"4d7e8ba7-70ae-45e4-b438-c668f354765a","uuid":"c9b70e53-77ec-49cf-8e2f-66166f4419af"}
[2026-03-13T18:28:28Z] [llm] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_016xZNteQag7KYj8vHVTuy82","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Cloche System Design\n     2→\n     3→## Overview\n     4→\n     5→Cloche is a system for grow-coding high quality applications. It provides containerized\n     6→environments for coding agents to operate in isolation, a workflow DSL for linking\n     7→agentic and script-driven tasks, validated code pipelines, and self-evolving tooling.\n     8→\n     9→This document describes the architecture for the MVP (v0.1).\n    10→\n    11→## System Components\n    12→\n    13→Cloche is a Go monorepo producing three binaries:\n    14→\n    15→```\n    16→cmd/\n    17→  cloche/         # CLI client (short-lived)\n    18→  cloched/        # Daemon/orchestrator (long-running)\n    19→  cloche-agent/   # In-container entrypoint (autonomous)\n    20→```\n    21→\n    22→### cloche (CLI)\n    23→\n    24→Short-lived process. Talks to `cloched` over gRPC (Unix socket locally, TCP remotely).\n    25→\n    26→Subcommands:\n    27→- `run <workflow>` — Launch a new workflow run\n    28→- `status [run-id]` — Check run status\n    29→- `logs <run-id>` — Stream logs from a running workflow (bidirectional gRPC stream)\n    30→- `stop <run-id>` — Cancel a running workflow (signals container with SIGTERM)\n    31→\n    32→Accepts prompt files or stdin input for user commands.\n    33→\n    34→### cloched (Daemon)\n    35→\n    36→Long-running process. Responsibilities:\n    37→- Launch and manage Docker containers for workflow runs\n    38→- Listen to status streams from running agents\n    39→- Record captures (step inputs, outputs, results, logs)\n    40→- Expose gRPC API for the CLI\n    41→- Persist state via pluggable storage (SQLite initially)\n    42→\n    43→The daemon does NOT interpret workflow logic. It knows \"container X is running workflow Y\"\n    44→and collects status. The agent is self-directing.\n    45→\n    46→### cloche-agent (In-Container Runtime)\n    47→\n    48→Autonomous process running inside the Docker container. Responsibilities:\n    49→- Parse the workflow DSL (workflow files live in the codebase)\n    50→- Walk the workflow graph, executing steps and following results\n    51→- Invoke coding agents (Claude Code, custom commands) and scripts\n    52→- Stream structured status events back to `cloched`\n    53→- Run to completion (`done` or `abort`) without human intervention\n    54→\n    55→The agent is told which workflow to execute at launch. It handles everything else.\n    56→\n    57→## Communication\n    58→\n    59→### CLI <-> Daemon: gRPC\n    60→\n    61→- Protobuf contracts define the API (the API is the spec)\n    62→- Bidirectional streaming for `logs` (tail container output in real-time)\n    63→- Unix socket for local communication, TCP for remote\n    64→\n    65→### Agent <-> Daemon: Structured JSON over stdout\n    66→\n    67→- The agent writes JSON-lines to stdout with status updates\n    68→- `cloched` attaches to the container's stdout stream via Docker API\n    69→- Messages include: step started, step completed (with result name), logs, errors\n    70→- Kill/cancel: daemon sends SIGTERM to container, agent handles graceful shutdown\n    71→\n    72→## Workflow DSL\n    73→\n    74→### Vocabulary\n    75→\n    76→| Concept  | Description                                                        |\n    77→|----------|--------------------------------------------------------------------|\n    78→| workflow | A named graph of steps connected by result wiring                  |\n    79→| step     | A unit of work (type: `agent` or `script`)                         |\n    80→| result   | A named outcome reported by a step (e.g. \"success\", \"fail\")       |\n    81→| wiring   | Maps a step's result to the next step                              |\n    82→| done     | Built-in terminal step indicating successful completion            |\n    83→| abort    | Built-in terminal step indicating failure (reports error and exits)|\n    84→\n    85→### Syntax\n    86→\n    87→```\n    88→workflow \"implement-feature\" {\n    89→  step code {\n    90→    prompt = file(\"prompts/implement.md\")\n    91→    container {\n    92→      image = \"cloche/agent:latest\"\n    93→      network_allow = [\"docs.python.org\", \"internal-docs.company.com\"]\n    94→    }\n    95→    results = [success, fail, retry_with_feedback]\n    96→  }\n    97→\n    98→  step check {\n    99→    run = \"make test && make lint\"\n   100→    results = [pass, fail]\n   101→  }\n   102→\n   103→  step review {\n   104→    prompt = file(\"prompts/review.md\")\n   105→    input = step.code.output\n   106→    results = [approved, changes_requested]\n   107→  }\n   108→\n   109→  code:success -> check\n   110→  code:fail -> abort\n   111→  code:retry_with_feedback -> code\n   112→\n   113→  check:pass -> review\n   114→  check:fail -> code:retry_with_feedback\n   115→\n   116→  review:approved -> done\n   117→  review:changes_requested -> code\n   118→}\n   119→```\n   120→\n   121→### Key Properties\n   122→\n   123→- Step type is inferred from content: `prompt` field → agent step, `run` field → script step.\n   124→- Steps declare which results they can emit. The step decides at runtime which result to report.\n   125→- Wiring is separate from step definitions. This enables runtime injection of new steps\n   126→  (the self-evolution feature) — insert a new check between existing steps by rewiring,\n   127→  without modifying either step.\n   128→- `file()` loads external content (prompt files, scripts).\n   129→- Step inputs can reference other step outputs (`step.code.output`).\n   130→- The graph engine validates at parse time: all declared results are wired, no orphan steps,\n   131→  entry point exists.\n   132→\n   133→## Hexagonal Architecture\n   134→\n   135→The core domain is independent of Docker, gRPC, SQLite, or any other infrastructure.\n   136→\n   137→### Domain\n   138→\n   139→```\n   140→internal/domain/\n   141→  workflow.go    # Workflow, Step, Result, Graph types\n   142→  run.go         # Run, RunState, StepExecution types\n   143→  capture.go     # CapturedInput, CapturedOutput for replay\n   144→```\n   145→\n   146→### Ports (interfaces)\n   147→\n   148→```\n   149→internal/ports/\n   150→  store.go       # RunStore, WorkflowStore, CaptureStore\n   151→  container.go   # ContainerRuntime (start, stop, attach, logs)\n   152→  agent.go       # AgentAdapter (how to invoke an agent)\n   153→  notifier.go    # StatusNotifier (how to report progress)\n   154→```\n   155→\n   156→### Adapters (implementations)\n   157→\n   158→```\n   159→internal/adapters/\n   160→  docker/        # ContainerRuntime via Docker API\n   161→  sqlite/        # Store implementations via SQLite\n   162→  grpc/          # gRPC server (daemon) and client (CLI)\n   163→  agents/\n   164→    claudecode/  # AgentAdapter for Claude Code\n   165→    generic/     # AgentAdapter for arbitrary commands\n   166→```\n   167→\n   168→### Key Interfaces\n   169→\n   170→- **ContainerRuntime** — Start/stop containers, attach to stdout, copy files in/out.\n   171→  Docker today, Podman or Firecracker later.\n   172→- **RunStore** — Persist run state (active step, reported results, timestamps).\n   173→- **CaptureStore** — Store step inputs/outputs for replay. Git refs serve as pointers\n   174→  to file states; metadata lives in the store.\n   175→- **AgentAdapter** — Translates between Cloche's step protocol and a specific agent's\n   176→  interface. Claude Code adapter knows how to invoke `claude` CLI. Generic adapter runs\n   177→  any command.\n   178→- **StatusNotifier** — How the agent reports progress. Stdout JSON-lines initially.\n   179→\n   180→## Container Model\n   181→\n   182→### One Container Per Workflow Run\n   183→\n   184→A container is spun up for a workflow run. All steps execute inside the same container.\n   185→File state accumulates naturally across steps (agent modifies code, then test script\n   186→runs against those modifications).\n   187→\n   188→### Lifecycle\n   189→\n   190→1. `cloched` pulls/builds the container image\n   191→2. Copies project files into the container at `/workspace`\n   192→3. Starts the container with `cloche-agent` as entrypoint, passing the workflow name\n   193→4. `cloche-agent` parses the workflow, walks the graph, executes steps\n   194→5. Agent streams status events to `cloched` via stdout\n   195→6. At step boundaries, modified files are pushed to the host via git (agent-specific branch)\n   196→7. On completion (`done`/`abort`), container is stopped\n   197→\n   198→### File Extraction via Git\n   199→\n   200→The container's git remote is configured to push to the host repository. Each run pushes\n   201→to a unique branch (e.g. `cloche/run-<id>/step-<name>`). This provides:\n   202→- Full git history of what the agent did\n   203→- Trivial diffs between input and output states\n   204→- Clean branch-per-step organization\n   205→- No bind mounts (maintains isolation)\n   206→\n   207→### Security Boundaries\n   208→\n   209→1. **Filesystem** — No access beyond `/workspace`. Copy-in at start, git push for extraction.\n   210→2. **Network** — `--network none` by default. If `network_allow` is specified, Cloche creates\n   211→   a custom Docker network restricting egress to allowlisted domains via DNS proxy.\n   212→3. **Environment** — Configured in Dockerfile/image. Cloche does not inject env vars.\n   213→\n   214→## Capture System\n   215→\n   216→Each step execution is captured for later inspection and replay.\n   217→\n   218→### What Gets Captured\n   219→\n   220→- Step config (prompt, type, container settings)\n   221→- Input state (git ref of what was provided to the step)\n   222→- Output state (git ref of what the step produced)\n   223→- Result reported (which result name)\n   224→- Stdout/stderr logs\n   225→- Timing metadata\n   226→\n   227→### Storage\n   228→\n   229→Metadata in the store (SQLite initially). Git refs serve as pointers to actual file\n   230→states — no duplication of file content.\n   231→\n   232→## MVP Scope (v0.1)\n   233→\n   234→### In Scope\n   235→\n   236→- `cloche` CLI: `run`, `status`, `logs`, `stop`\n   237→- `cloched` daemon: container lifecycle, status collection, gRPC API, SQLite store\n   238→- `cloche-agent`: DSL parser, graph engine, agent/script execution, status reporting\n   239→- Workflow DSL: steps, results, wiring, `done`/`abort` terminals, `file()` references\n   240→- Container model: Docker, copy-in project files, git push for extraction, network allowlist\n   241→- Agent adapters: Generic (run a command) + Claude Code\n   242→- Capture system: Record step inputs/outputs/results\n   243→\n   244→### Post-MVP\n   245→\n   246→- Self-evolution: failure pattern analysis, automatic step injection into workflows\n   247→- Replay system: partial/full/dry replay of captured runs\n   248→- Auto-split commits into stacked branches\n   249→- Additional agent adapters\n   250→- Alternative storage backends (Postgres, DynamoDB)\n   251→- Alternative container runtimes (Podman, Firecracker)\n   252→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_014nB1uYcqdGQDnmCdayJAtm","session_id":"4d7e8ba7-70ae-45e4-b438-c668f354765a","uuid":"76c245ca-f0a2-4e35-9168-5516b247e99a"}
[2026-03-13T18:28:28Z] [llm] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01XRVRpqvEB56BukVSQmDx21","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package grpc\n     2→\n     3→import (\n     4→\t\"bufio\"\n     5→\t\"context\"\n     6→\t\"encoding/json\"\n     7→\t\"fmt\"\n     8→\t\"log\"\n     9→\t\"os\"\n    10→\t\"os/exec\"\n    11→\t\"path/filepath\"\n    12→\t\"strings\"\n    13→\t\"sync\"\n    14→\t\"time\"\n    15→\n    16→\tpb \"github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/api/clochepb\"\n    17→\t\"github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/internal/adapters/docker\"\n    18→\t\"github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/internal/adapters/web\"\n    19→\t\"github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/internal/config\"\n    20→\t\"github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/internal/domain\"\n    21→\t\"github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/internal/evolution\"\n    22→\t\"github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/internal/host\"\n    23→\t\"github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/internal/logstream\"\n    24→\t\"github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/internal/ports\"\n    25→\t\"github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/internal/protocol\"\n    26→\trpcgrpc \"google.golang.org/grpc\"\n    27→\t\"google.golang.org/grpc/metadata\"\n    28→)\n    29→\n    30→type ClocheServer struct {\n    31→\tpb.UnimplementedClocheServiceServer\n    32→\tstore        ports.RunStore\n    33→\tcaptures     ports.CaptureStore\n    34→\tlogStore     ports.LogStore\n    35→\tcontainer    ports.ContainerRuntime\n    36→\tdefaultImage string\n    37→\tevolution    *evolution.Trigger\n    38→\tlogBroadcast *logstream.Broadcaster\n    39→\tshutdownFn   func()\n    40→\tmu           sync.Mutex\n    41→\trunIDs       map[string]string      // run_id -> container_id\n    42→\tloops        map[string]*host.Loop  // project_dir -> orchestration loop\n    43→}\n    44→\n    45→func NewClocheServer(store ports.RunStore, container ports.ContainerRuntime) *ClocheServer {\n    46→\treturn &ClocheServer{\n    47→\t\tstore:     store,\n    48→\t\tcontainer: container,\n    49→\t\trunIDs:    make(map[string]string),\n    50→\t\tloops:     make(map[string]*host.Loop),\n    51→\t}\n    52→}\n    53→\n    54→func NewClocheServerWithCaptures(store ports.RunStore, captures ports.CaptureStore, container ports.ContainerRuntime, defaultImage string) *ClocheServer {\n    55→\treturn &ClocheServer{\n    56→\t\tstore:        store,\n    57→\t\tcaptures:     captures,\n    58→\t\tcontainer:    container,\n    59→\t\tdefaultImage: defaultImage,\n    60→\t\trunIDs:       make(map[string]string),\n    61→\t\tloops:        make(map[string]*host.Loop),\n    62→\t}\n    63→}\n    64→\n    65→// SetLogStore attaches a log store to the server for indexing extracted log files.\n    66→func (s *ClocheServer) SetLogStore(ls ports.LogStore) {\n    67→\ts.logStore = ls\n    68→}\n    69→\n    70→\n    71→// SetEvolution attaches an evolution trigger to the server.\n    72→func (s *ClocheServer) SetEvolution(trigger *evolution.Trigger) {\n    73→\ts.evolution = trigger\n    74→}\n    75→\n    76→// SetLogBroadcaster attaches a log broadcaster for live-streaming LLM output.\n    77→func (s *ClocheServer) SetLogBroadcaster(b *logstream.Broadcaster) {\n    78→\ts.logBroadcast = b\n    79→}\n    80→\n    81→// SetShutdownFunc sets the callback invoked when the Shutdown RPC is called.\n    82→func (s *ClocheServer) SetShutdownFunc(fn func()) {\n    83→\ts.shutdownFn = fn\n    84→}\n    85→\n    86→func (s *ClocheServer) RunWorkflow(ctx context.Context, req *pb.RunWorkflowRequest) (*pb.RunWorkflowResponse, error) {\n    87→\tif s.container == nil {\n    88→\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"no container runtime configured\")\n    89→\t}\n    90→\n    91→\t// Generate a unique run ID, retrying on collision\n    92→\tvar runID string\n    93→\tfor attempts := 0; attempts < 10; attempts++ {\n    94→\t\trunID = domain.GenerateRunID(req.WorkflowName)\n    95→\t\texisting, err := s.store.GetRun(ctx, runID)\n    96→\t\tif err != nil {\n    97→\t\t\tbreak // ID is free\n    98→\t\t}\n    99→\t\t// Reuse if completed more than 1 hour ago\n   100→\t\tif !existing.CompletedAt.IsZero() && time.Since(existing.CompletedAt) > time.Hour {\n   101→\t\t\t_ = s.store.DeleteRun(ctx, runID)\n   102→\t\t\tbreak\n   103→\t\t}\n   104→\t}\n   105→\n   106→\t// Write prompt to .cloche/<run-id>/prompt.txt (run-specific to avoid conflicts)\n   107→\tif req.Prompt != \"\" {\n   108→\t\tclocheDir := filepath.Join(req.ProjectDir, \".cloche\", runID)\n   109→\t\tif err := os.MkdirAll(clocheDir, 0755); err != nil {\n   110→\t\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"creating .cloche dir: %w\", err)\n   111→\t\t}\n   112→\t\tif err := os.WriteFile(filepath.Join(clocheDir, \"prompt.txt\"), []byte(req.Prompt), 0644); err != nil {\n   113→\t\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"writing prompt: %w\", err)\n   114→\t\t}\n   115→\t}\n   116→\trun := domain.NewRun(runID, req.WorkflowName)\n   117→\trun.ProjectDir = req.ProjectDir\n   118→\trun.Title = req.Title\n   119→\tif err := s.store.CreateRun(ctx, run); err != nil {\n   120→\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"creating run: %w\", err)\n   121→\t}\n   122→\n   123→\t// Resolve image: request-level override, then server default\n   124→\timage := req.Image\n   125→\tif image == \"\" {\n   126→\t\timage = s.defaultImage\n   127→\t}\n   128→\n   129→\t// Launch container start + tracking in background so the RPC returns immediately.\n   130→\t// The run stays in \"pending\" state until the container is up.\n   131→\tgo s.launchAndTrack(runID, image, req.KeepContainer, req)\n   132→\n   133→\treturn &pb.RunWorkflowResponse{RunId: runID}, nil\n   134→}\n   135→\n   136→// launchAndTrack starts the container and then tracks it to completion.\n   137→// It runs in a background goroutine with its own context, independent of the\n   138→// RPC context which may be cancelled after RunWorkflow returns.\n   139→func (s *ClocheServer) launchAndTrack(runID, image string, keepContainer bool, req *pb.RunWorkflowRequest) {\n   140→\tctx := context.Background()\n   141→\n   142→\t// Auto-rebuild image if the project Dockerfile has changed since last build.\n   143→\tif ensurer, ok := s.container.(ports.ImageEnsurer); ok {\n   144→\t\tif err := ensurer.EnsureImage(ctx, req.ProjectDir, image); err != nil {\n   145→\t\t\trun, _ := s.store.GetRun(ctx, runID)\n   146→\t\t\tif run != nil {\n   147→\t\t\t\trun.Fail(fmt.Sprintf(\"failed to ensure image: %v\", err))\n   148→\t\t\t\t_ = s.store.UpdateRun(ctx, run)\n   149→\t\t\t}\n   150→\t\t\tlog.Printf(\"run %s: failed to ensure image: %v\", runID, err)\n   151→\t\t\t\treturn\n   152→\t\t}\n   153→\t}\n   154→\n   155→\tbaseSHA := gitHEAD(req.ProjectDir)\n   156→\n   157→\tcontainerID, err := s.container.Start(ctx, ports.ContainerConfig{\n   158→\t\tImage:        image,\n   159→\t\tWorkflowName: req.WorkflowName,\n   160→\t\tProjectDir:   req.ProjectDir,\n   161→\t\tRunID:        runID,\n   162→\t\tNetworkAllow: []string{\"*\"},\n   163→\t})\n   164→\tif err != nil {\n   165→\t\trun, _ := s.store.GetRun(ctx, runID)\n   166→\t\tif run != nil {\n   167→\t\t\trun.Fail(fmt.Sprintf(\"failed to start container: %v\", err))\n   168→\t\t\t_ = s.store.UpdateRun(ctx, run)\n   169→\t\t}\n   170→\t\tlog.Printf(\"run %s: failed to start container: %v\", runID, err)\n   171→\t\treturn\n   172→\t}\n   173→\n   174→\ts.mu.Lock()\n   175→\ts.runIDs[runID] = containerID\n   176→\ts.mu.Unlock()\n   177→\n   178→\trun, _ := s.store.GetRun(ctx, runID)\n   179→\tif run != nil {\n   180→\t\trun.Start()\n   181→\t\trun.ContainerID = containerID\n   182→\t\trun.BaseSHA = baseSHA\n   183→\t\t_ = s.store.UpdateRun(ctx, run)\n   184→\t}\n   185→\n   186→\ts.trackRun(runID, containerID, req.ProjectDir, req.WorkflowName, keepContainer)\n   187→}\n   188→\n   189→func (s *ClocheServer) trackRun(runID, containerID, projectDir, workflowName string, keepContainer bool) {\n   190→\tctx := context.Background()\n   191→\n   192→\t// Attach to agent output\n   193→\treader, err := s.container.AttachOutput(ctx, containerID)\n   194→\tif err != nil {\n   195→\t\tlog.Printf(\"failed to attach to output for run %s: %v\", runID, err)\n   196→\t\t\treturn\n   197→\t}\n   198→\n   199→\t// Parse JSON-lines status messages\n   200→\tvar reportedResult string // captured from MsgRunCompleted, persisted after branch extraction\n   201→\tscanner := bufio.NewScanner(reader)\n   202→\tscanner.Buffer(make([]byte, 0, 256*1024), 1024*1024) // 1MB max to handle large log messages\n   203→\tfor scanner.Scan() {\n   204→\t\tvar msg protocol.StatusMessage\n   205→\t\tif err := json.Unmarshal(scanner.Bytes(), &msg); err != nil {\n   206→\t\t\tcontinue\n   207→\t\t}\n   208→\n   209→\t\t// Fast path: log messages don't need store interaction.\n   210→\t\tif msg.Type == protocol.MsgLog {\n   211→\t\t\tif s.logBroadcast != nil {\n   212→\t\t\t\ts.logBroadcast.Publish(runID, logstream.LogLine{\n   213→\t\t\t\t\tTimestamp: msg.Timestamp.Format(time.RFC3339),\n   214→\t\t\t\t\tType:      \"llm\",\n   215→\t\t\t\t\tContent:   msg.Message,\n   216→\t\t\t\t\tStepName:  msg.StepName,\n   217→\t\t\t\t})\n   218→\t\t\t}\n   219→\t\t\tcontinue\n   220→\t\t}\n   221→\n   222→\t\trun, err := s.store.GetRun(ctx, runID)\n   223→\t\tif err != nil {\n   224→\t\t\tcontinue\n   225→\t\t}\n   226→\n   227→\t\tswitch msg.Type {\n   228→\t\tcase protocol.MsgStepStarted:\n   229→\t\t\trun.RecordStepStart(msg.StepName)\n   230→\t\t\tif s.captures != nil {\n   231→\t\t\t\t_ = s.captures.SaveCapture(ctx, runID, &domain.StepExecution{\n   232→\t\t\t\t\tStepName:  msg.StepName,\n   233→\t\t\t\t\tStartedAt: msg.Timestamp,\n   234→\t\t\t\t})\n   235→\t\t\t}\n   236→\t\t\tif s.logBroadcast != nil {\n   237→\t\t\t\ts.logBroadcast.Publish(runID, logstream.LogLine{\n   238→\t\t\t\t\tTimestamp: msg.Timestamp.Format(time.RFC3339),\n   239→\t\t\t\t\tType:      \"status\",\n   240→\t\t\t\t\tContent:   \"step_started: \" + msg.StepName,\n   241→\t\t\t\t\tStepName:  msg.StepName,\n   242→\t\t\t\t})\n   243→\t\t\t}\n   244→\t\tcase protocol.MsgStepCompleted:\n   245→\t\t\trun.RecordStepComplete(msg.StepName, msg.Result)\n   246→\t\t\tif s.captures != nil {\n   247→\t\t\t\t_ = s.captures.SaveCapture(ctx, runID, &domain.StepExecution{\n   248→\t\t\t\t\tStepName:    msg.StepName,\n   249→\t\t\t\t\tResult:      msg.Result,\n   250→\t\t\t\t\tCompletedAt: msg.Timestamp,\n   251→\t\t\t\t})\n   252→\t\t\t}\n   253→\t\t\tif s.logBroadcast != nil {\n   254→\t\t\t\ts.logBroadcast.Publish(runID, logstream.LogLine{\n   255→\t\t\t\t\tTimestamp: msg.Timestamp.Format(time.RFC3339),\n   256→\t\t\t\t\tType:      \"status\",\n   257→\t\t\t\t\tContent:   \"step_completed: \" + msg.StepName + \" -> \" + msg.Result,\n   258→\t\t\t\t\tStepName:  msg.StepName,\n   259→\t\t\t\t})\n   260→\t\t\t}\n   261→\t\tcase protocol.MsgRunTitle:\n   262→\t\t\tif run.Title == \"\" {\n   263→\t\t\t\trun.Title = msg.Message\n   264→\t\t\t}\n   265→\t\tcase protocol.MsgRunCompleted:\n   266→\t\t\treportedResult = msg.Result\n   267→\t\t\tcontinue // Don't persist terminal state yet; branch extraction must finish first\n   268→\t\t}\n   269→\n   270→\t\t_ = s.store.UpdateRun(ctx, run)\n   271→\t}\n   272→\treader.Close()\n   273→\n   274→\t// Signal live-stream subscribers that this run is done.\n   275→\tif s.logBroadcast != nil {\n   276→\t\ts.logBroadcast.Finish(runID)\n   277→\t}\n   278→\n   279→\t// Wait for process exit\n   280→\texitCode, err := s.container.Wait(ctx, containerID)\n   281→\tif err != nil {\n   282→\t\tlog.Printf(\"error waiting for run %s: %v\", runID, err)\n   283→\t}\n   284→\n   285→\t// Extract step output files from container before it's removed\n   286→\toutputDst := filepath.Join(projectDir, \".cloche\", runID, \"output\")\n   287→\tif err := os.MkdirAll(outputDst, 0755); err == nil {\n   288→\t\tif cpErr := s.container.CopyFrom(ctx, containerID, \"/workspace/.cloche/output/.\", outputDst); cpErr != nil {\n   289→\t\t\tlog.Printf(\"run %s: failed to extract output: %v\", runID, cpErr)\n   290→\t\t}\n   291→\t}\n   292→\n   293→\t// Capture full container stdout/stderr before the container is removed\n   294→\tif logs, logErr := s.container.Logs(ctx, containerID); logErr == nil && logs != \"\" {\n   295→\t\tcontainerLogPath := filepath.Join(outputDst, \"container.log\")\n   296→\t\tif writeErr := os.WriteFile(containerLogPath, []byte(logs), 0644); writeErr != nil {\n   297→\t\t\tlog.Printf(\"run %s: failed to write container.log: %v\", runID, writeErr)\n   298→\t\t}\n   299→\t}\n   300→\n   301→\t// Index extracted log files in the log store\n   302→\tif s.logStore != nil {\n   303→\t\ts.indexLogFiles(ctx, runID, outputDst)\n   304→\t}\n   305→\n   306→\t// Extract results to git branch BEFORE finalizing state, so that\n   307→\t// WaitRun callers (e.g. host workflow merge step) see branches exist\n   308→\t// before the run is marked complete.\n   309→\tresultLabel := reportedResult\n   310→\tif resultLabel == \"\" {\n   311→\t\tif exitCode == 0 {\n   312→\t\t\tresultLabel = \"succeeded\"\n   313→\t\t} else {\n   314→\t\t\tresultLabel = \"failed\"\n   315→\t\t}\n   316→\t}\n   317→\t{\n   318→\t\textractRun, _ := s.store.GetRun(ctx, runID)\n   319→\t\tif extractRun != nil && extractRun.BaseSHA != \"\" {\n   320→\t\t\tlog.Printf(\"run %s: extracting results to branch cloche/%s (baseSHA=%s)\", runID, runID, extractRun.BaseSHA)\n   321→\t\t\tif err := docker.ExtractResults(ctx, containerID, extractRun.ProjectDir, runID, extractRun.BaseSHA, workflowName, resultLabel); err != nil {\n   322→\t\t\t\tlog.Printf(\"run %s: failed to extract results to branch: %v\", runID, err)\n   323→\t\t\t} else {\n   324→\t\t\t\tlog.Printf(\"run %s: branch cloche/%s created successfully\", runID, runID)\n   325→\t\t\t}\n   326→\t\t} else {\n   327→\t\t\tlog.Printf(\"run %s: skipping branch extraction (baseSHA empty or run not found)\", runID)\n   328→\t\t}\n   329→\t}\n   330→\n   331→\t// Now finalize run state\n   332→\trun, err := s.store.GetRun(ctx, runID)\n   333→\tif err != nil {\n   334→\t\treturn\n   335→\t}\n   336→\tif run.State == domain.RunStateRunning {\n   337→\t\tif reportedResult == \"succeeded\" {\n   338→\t\t\trun.Complete(domain.RunStateSucceeded)\n   339→\t\t} else if reportedResult != \"\" {\n   340→\t\t\trun.Complete(domain.RunStateFailed)\n   341→\t\t} else if exitCode == 0 {\n   342→\t\t\trun.Complete(domain.RunStateSucceeded)\n   343→\t\t} else {\n   344→\t\t\trun.Fail(fmt.Sprintf(\"container exited with code %d\", exitCode))\n   345→\t\t}\n   346→\t\t_ = s.store.UpdateRun(ctx, run)\n   347→\t}\n   348→\n   349→\t// Fire evolution trigger if configured\n   350→\tif s.evolution != nil {\n   351→\t\ts.evolution.Fire(projectDir, workflowName, runID)\n   352→\t}\n   353→\n   354→\t// Merge is handled as a workflow step in host.cloche, not here.\n   355→\n   356→\t// Container retention policy:\n   357→\t// - Failed runs: always keep the container for debugging\n   358→\t// - Successful runs + --keep-container: keep the container\n   359→\t// - Successful runs without --keep-container: remove the container\n   360→\trunFinal, _ := s.store.GetRun(ctx, runID)\n   361→\trunFailed := runFinal != nil && (runFinal.State == domain.RunStateFailed || runFinal.State == domain.RunStateCancelled)\n   362→\n   363→\tif keepContainer || runFailed {\n   364→\t\treason := \"--keep-container\"\n   365→\t\tif runFailed {\n   366→\t\t\treason = \"run failed\"\n   367→\t\t}\n   368→\t\tlog.Printf(\"run %s: keeping container %s (%s)\", runID, containerID, reason)\n   369→\t\tif runFinal != nil {\n   370→\t\t\trunFinal.ContainerKept = true\n   371→\t\t\t_ = s.store.UpdateRun(ctx, runFinal)\n   372→\t\t}\n   373→\t} else {\n   374→\t\tif err := s.container.Remove(ctx, containerID); err != nil {\n   375→\t\t\tlog.Printf(\"run %s: failed to remove container %s: %v\", runID, containerID, err)\n   376→\t\t} else {\n   377→\t\t\tlog.Printf(\"run %s: removed container %s\", runID, containerID)\n   378→\t\t}\n   379→\t}\n   380→\n   381→\t// Cleanup mapping\n   382→\ts.mu.Lock()\n   383→\tdelete(s.runIDs, runID)\n   384→\ts.mu.Unlock()\n   385→}\n   386→\n   387→func (s *ClocheServer) ListRuns(ctx context.Context, req *pb.ListRunsRequest) (*pb.ListRunsResponse, error) {\n   388→\tfilter := domain.RunListFilter{\n   389→\t\tProjectDir: req.ProjectDir,\n   390→\t\tState:      domain.RunState(req.State),\n   391→\t\tTaskID:     req.TaskId,\n   392→\t\tLimit:      int(req.Limit),\n   393→\t}\n   394→\n   395→\t// When no project filter and not --all, default to last hour\n   396→\tif filter.ProjectDir == \"\" && !req.All {\n   397→\t\tfilter.Since = time.Now().Add(-1 * time.Hour)\n   398→\t}\n   399→\n   400→\truns, err := s.store.ListRunsFiltered(ctx, filter)\n   401→\tif err != nil {\n   402→\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"listing runs: %w\", err)\n   403→\t}\n   404→\n   405→\tresp := &pb.ListRunsResponse{}\n   406→\tfor _, run := range runs {\n   407→\t\tresp.Runs = append(resp.Runs, &pb.RunSummary{\n   408→\t\t\tRunId:        run.ID,\n   409→\t\t\tWorkflowName: run.WorkflowName,\n   410→\t\t\tState:        string(run.State),\n   411→\t\t\tStartedAt:    run.StartedAt.String(),\n   412→\t\t\tErrorMessage: run.ErrorMessage,\n   413→\t\t\tContainerId:  run.ContainerID,\n   414→\t\t\tTitle:        run.Title,\n   415→\t\t\tIsHost:       run.IsHost,\n   416→\t\t\tProjectDir:   run.ProjectDir,\n   417→\t\t})\n   418→\t}\n   419→\treturn resp, nil\n   420→}\n   421→\n   422→func (s *ClocheServer) GetStatus(ctx context.Context, req *pb.GetStatusRequest) (*pb.GetStatusResponse, error) {\n   423→\trun, err := s.store.GetRun(ctx, req.RunId)\n   424→\tif err != nil {\n   425→\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"getting run: %w\", err)\n   426→\t}\n   427→\n   428→\tresp := &pb.GetStatusResponse{\n   429→\t\tRunId:        run.ID,\n   430→\t\tWorkflowName: run.WorkflowName,\n   431→\t\tState:        string(run.State),\n   432→\t\tCurrentStep:  strings.Join(run.ActiveSteps, \",\"),\n   433→\t\tErrorMessage: run.ErrorMessage,\n   434→\t\tContainerId:  run.ContainerID,\n   435→\t\tTitle:        run.Title,\n   436→\t\tIsHost:       run.IsHost,\n   437→\t}\n   438→\n   439→\t// Check container liveness\n   440→\tif run.ContainerID != \"\" && s.container != nil {\n   441→\t\tif cs, err := s.container.Inspect(ctx, run.ContainerID); err == nil {\n   442→\t\t\tresp.ContainerAlive = cs.Running\n   443→\t\t\tif !cs.Running && !cs.FinishedAt.IsZero() {\n   444→\t\t\t\tresp.ContainerDeadSince = cs.FinishedAt.Format(time.RFC3339Nano)\n   445→\t\t\t}\n   446→\t\t}\n   447→\t}\n   448→\n   449→\t// Load step executions from captures store if available\n   450→\tif s.captures != nil {\n   451→\t\tcaptures, err := s.captures.GetCaptures(ctx, req.RunId)\n   452→\t\tif err == nil {\n   453→\t\t\tfor _, exec := range captures {\n   454→\t\t\t\tresp.StepExecutions = append(resp.StepExecutions, &pb.StepExecutionStatus{\n   455→\t\t\t\t\tStepName:    exec.StepName,\n   456→\t\t\t\t\tResult:      exec.Result,\n   457→\t\t\t\t\tStartedAt:   exec.StartedAt.String(),\n   458→\t\t\t\t\tCompletedAt: exec.CompletedAt.String(),\n   459→\t\t\t\t})\n   460→\t\t\t}\n   461→\t\t}\n   462→\t} else {\n   463→\t\tfor _, exec := range run.StepExecutions {\n   464→\t\t\tresp.StepExecutions = append(resp.StepExecutions, &pb.StepExecutionStatus{\n   465→\t\t\t\tStepName:    exec.StepName,\n   466→\t\t\t\tResult:      exec.Result,\n   467→\t\t\t\tStartedAt:   exec.StartedAt.String(),\n   468→\t\t\t\tCompletedAt: exec.CompletedAt.String(),\n   469→\t\t\t})\n   470→\t\t}\n   471→\t}\n   472→\n   473→\treturn resp, nil\n   474→}\n   475→\n   476→func (s *ClocheServer) StreamLogs(req *pb.StreamLogsRequest, stream rpcgrpc.ServerStreamingServer[pb.LogEntry]) error {\n   477→\tctx := stream.Context()\n   478→\n   479→\t// Check for follow mode via gRPC metadata.\n   480→\tfollow := followFromContext(ctx)\n   481→\n   482→\t// Verify run exists\n   483→\trun, err := s.store.GetRun(ctx, req.RunId)\n   484→\tif err != nil {\n   485→\t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"run %q not found: %w\", req.RunId, err)\n   486→\t}\n   487→\n   488→\t// If step_name or log_type filter is set, serve content directly from the log index\n   489→\tif req.StepName != \"\" || req.LogType != \"\" {\n   490→\t\treturn s.streamFilteredLogs(ctx, req, run, stream)\n   491→\t}\n   492→\n   493→\tisActive := run.State == domain.RunStateRunning || run.State == domain.RunStatePending\n   494→\n   495→\t// With -f on an active run: send existing logs then tail live output.\n   496→\tif follow && isActive && s.logBroadcast != nil {\n   497→\t\treturn s.streamFollowLogs(req.RunId, run, stream)\n   498→\t}\n   499→\n   500→\t// Without -f on an active run: snapshot existing logs and return.\n   501→\t// (Legacy callers that relied on implicit live streaming should use -f.)\n   502→\t// With -f on a completed run: same as without -f — no new lines will arrive.\n   503→\n   504→\t// Check for full.log first — if it exists, serve it as the unified log\n   505→\tfullLogPath := filepath.Join(run.ProjectDir, \".cloche\", req.RunId, \"output\", \"full.log\")\n   506→\tif data, readErr := os.ReadFile(fullLogPath); readErr == nil && len(data) > 0 {\n   507→\t\tif err := stream.Send(&pb.LogEntry{\n   508→\t\t\tType:    \"full_log\",\n   509→\t\t\tMessage: string(data),\n   510→\t\t}); err != nil {\n   511→\t\t\treturn err\n   512→\t\t}\n   513→\t\tif !isActive {\n   514→\t\t\tif err := stream.Send(&pb.LogEntry{\n   515→\t\t\t\tType:      \"run_completed\",\n   516→\t\t\t\tResult:    string(run.State),\n   517→\t\t\t\tTimestamp: run.CompletedAt.String(),\n   518→\t\t\t\tMessage:   run.ErrorMessage,\n   519→\t\t\t}); err != nil {\n   520→\t\t\t\treturn err\n   521→\t\t\t}\n   522→\t\t}\n   523→\t\treturn nil\n   524→\t}\n   525→\n   526→\tif s.captures == nil {\n   527→\t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"captures store not configured\")\n   528→\t}\n   529→\n   530→\t// Fall back to capture-based streaming\n   531→\tcaptures, err := s.captures.GetCaptures(ctx, req.RunId)\n   532→\tif err != nil {\n   533→\t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"getting captures: %w\", err)\n   534→\t}\n   535→\n   536→\tfor _, exec := range captures {\n   537→\t\t// Captures are stored as separate rows: one for step_started (no Result)\n   538→\t\t// and one for step_completed (has Result).\n   539→\t\tif exec.Result == \"\" {\n   540→\t\t\tentry := &pb.LogEntry{\n   541→\t\t\t\tType:      \"step_started\",\n   542→\t\t\t\tStepName:  exec.StepName,\n   543→\t\t\t\tTimestamp: exec.StartedAt.String(),\n   544→\t\t\t}\n   545→\t\t\tif err := stream.Send(entry); err != nil {\n   546→\t\t\t\treturn err\n   547→\t\t\t}\n   548→\t\t} else {\n   549→\t\t\t// Read step output from per-step output file.\n   550→\t\t\t// Container runs write .log, host runs write .out — try both.\n   551→\t\t\tvar output string\n   552→\t\t\tfor _, ext := range []string{\".log\", \".out\"} {\n   553→\t\t\t\toutputPath := filepath.Join(run.ProjectDir, \".cloche\", req.RunId, \"output\", exec.StepName+ext)\n   554→\t\t\t\tif data, err := os.ReadFile(outputPath); err == nil && len(data) > 0 {\n   555→\t\t\t\t\toutput = string(data)\n   556→\t\t\t\t\tbreak\n   557→\t\t\t\t}\n   558→\t\t\t}\n   559→\t\t\tentry := &pb.LogEntry{\n   560→\t\t\t\tType:      \"step_completed\",\n   561→\t\t\t\tStepName:  exec.StepName,\n   562→\t\t\t\tResult:    exec.Result,\n   563→\t\t\t\tTimestamp: exec.CompletedAt.String(),\n   564→\t\t\t\tMessage:   output,\n   565→\t\t\t}\n   566→\t\t\tif err := stream.Send(entry); err != nil {\n   567→\t\t\t\treturn err\n   568→\t\t\t}\n   569→\t\t}\n   570→\t}\n   571→\n   572→\t// Send run completion entry\n   573→\tif !isActive {\n   574→\t\tif err := stream.Send(&pb.LogEntry{\n   575→\t\t\tType:      \"run_completed\",\n   576→\t\t\tResult:    string(run.State),\n   577→\t\t\tTimestamp: run.CompletedAt.String(),\n   578→\t\t\tMessage:   run.ErrorMessage,\n   579→\t\t}); err != nil {\n   580→\t\t\treturn err\n   581→\t\t}\n   582→\t}\n   583→\n   584→\treturn nil\n   585→}\n   586→\n   587→// followFromContext checks for the follow flag in gRPC metadata.\n   588→func followFromContext(ctx context.Context) bool {\n   589→\tmd, ok := metadata.FromIncomingContext(ctx)\n   590→\tif !ok {\n   591→\t\treturn false\n   592→\t}\n   593→\tvals := md.Get(\"x-cloche-follow\")\n   594→\treturn len(vals) > 0 && vals[0] == \"true\"\n   595→}\n   596→\n   597→// streamFollowLogs sends existing log content then tails live output from the\n   598→// broadcaster. It combines snapshot + live streaming (like tail -f).\n   599→func (s *ClocheServer) streamFollowLogs(runID string, run *domain.Run, stream rpcgrpc.ServerStreamingServer[pb.LogEntry]) error {\n   600→\t// Subscribe first so we don't miss lines written between read and subscribe.\n   601→\tsub := s.logBroadcast.Subscribe(runID)\n   602→\tdefer s.logBroadcast.Unsubscribe(runID, sub)\n   603→\n   604→\t// Send existing full.log content if available.\n   605→\tfullLogPath := filepath.Join(run.ProjectDir, \".cloche\", runID, \"output\", \"full.log\")\n   606→\tif data, err := os.ReadFile(fullLogPath); err == nil && len(data) > 0 {\n   607→\t\tif err := stream.Send(&pb.LogEntry{\n   608→\t\t\tType:    \"full_log\",\n   609→\t\t\tMessage: string(data),\n   610→\t\t}); err != nil {\n   611→\t\t\treturn err\n   612→\t\t}\n   613→\t}\n   614→\n   615→\t// Now tail live output from the broadcaster.\n   616→\tctx := stream.Context()\n   617→\tfor {\n   618→\t\tselect {\n   619→\t\tcase <-ctx.Done():\n   620→\t\t\treturn ctx.Err()\n   621→\t\tcase line, ok := <-sub.C:\n   622→\t\t\tif !ok {\n   623→\t\t\t\t// Run completed — send terminal entry.\n   624→\t\t\t\tr, err := s.store.GetRun(context.Background(), runID)\n   625→\t\t\t\tif err == nil && r.State != domain.RunStateRunning && r.State != domain.RunStatePending {\n   626→\t\t\t\t\t_ = stream.Send(&pb.LogEntry{\n   627→\t\t\t\t\t\tType:      \"run_completed\",\n   628→\t\t\t\t\t\tResult:    string(r.State),\n   629→\t\t\t\t\t\tTimestamp: r.CompletedAt.String(),\n   630→\t\t\t\t\t\tMessage:   r.ErrorMessage,\n   631→\t\t\t\t\t})\n   632→\t\t\t\t}\n   633→\t\t\t\treturn nil\n   634→\t\t\t}\n   635→\t\t\tif err := stream.Send(&pb.LogEntry{\n   636→\t\t\t\tType:      \"log\",\n   637→\t\t\t\tStepName:  line.StepName,\n   638→\t\t\t\tMessage:   line.Content,\n   639→\t\t\t\tTimestamp: line.Timestamp,\n   640→\t\t\t}); err != nil {\n   641→\t\t\t\treturn err\n   642→\t\t\t}\n   643→\t\t}\n   644→\t}\n   645→}\n   646→\n   647→// streamFilteredLogs serves log content filtered by step name and/or log type.\n   648→// It uses the log index when available, falling back to file path conventions.\n   649→func (s *ClocheServer) streamFilteredLogs(ctx context.Context, req *pb.StreamLogsRequest, run *domain.Run, stream rpcgrpc.ServerStreamingServer[pb.LogEntry]) error {\n   650→\toutputDir := filepath.Join(run.ProjectDir, \".cloche\", req.RunId, \"output\")\n   651→\n   652→\t// Try log index first\n   653→\tif s.logStore != nil {\n   654→\t\tvar logFiles []*ports.LogFileEntry\n   655→\t\tvar err error\n   656→\n   657→\t\tif req.StepName != \"\" && req.LogType != \"\" {\n   658→\t\t\t// Filter by both step and type\n   659→\t\t\tlogFiles, err = s.logStore.GetLogFilesByStep(ctx, req.RunId, req.StepName)\n   660→\t\t\tif err == nil {\n   661→\t\t\t\tfiltered := logFiles[:0]\n   662→\t\t\t\tfor _, lf := range logFiles {\n   663→\t\t\t\t\tif lf.FileType == req.LogType {\n   664→\t\t\t\t\t\tfiltered = append(filtered, lf)\n   665→\t\t\t\t\t}\n   666→\t\t\t\t}\n   667→\t\t\t\tlogFiles = filtered\n   668→\t\t\t}\n   669→\t\t} else if req.StepName != \"\" {\n   670→\t\t\tlogFiles, err = s.logStore.GetLogFilesByStep(ctx, req.RunId, req.StepName)\n   671→\t\t} else {\n   672→\t\t\tlogFiles, err = s.logStore.GetLogFileByType(ctx, req.RunId, req.LogType)\n   673→\t\t}\n   674→\n   675→\t\tif err == nil && len(logFiles) > 0 {\n   676→\t\t\tfor _, lf := range logFiles {\n   677→\t\t\t\tdata, readErr := os.ReadFile(lf.FilePath)\n   678→\t\t\t\tif readErr != nil {\n   679→\t\t\t\t\tcontinue\n   680→\t\t\t\t}\n   681→\t\t\t\tif err := stream.Send(&pb.LogEntry{\n   682→\t\t\t\t\tType:     lf.FileType + \"_log\",\n   683→\t\t\t\t\tStepName: lf.StepName,\n   684→\t\t\t\t\tMessage:  string(data),\n   685→\t\t\t\t}); err != nil {\n   686→\t\t\t\t\treturn err\n   687→\t\t\t\t}\n   688→\t\t\t}\n   689→\t\t\treturn nil\n   690→\t\t}\n   691→\t}\n   692→\n   693→\t// Fall back to file path conventions\n   694→\tif req.StepName != \"\" {\n   695→\t\tvar logPath string\n   696→\t\tswitch req.LogType {\n   697→\t\tcase \"llm\":\n   698→\t\t\tlogPath = filepath.Join(outputDir, \"llm-\"+req.StepName+\".log\")\n   699→\t\tdefault:\n   700→\t\t\tlogPath = filepath.Join(outputDir, req.StepName+\".log\")\n   701→\t\t}\n   702→\n   703→\t\tdata, err := os.ReadFile(logPath)\n   704→\t\tif err != nil {\n   705→\t\t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"log file not found for step %q: %w\", req.StepName, err)\n   706→\t\t}\n   707→\t\treturn stream.Send(&pb.LogEntry{\n   708→\t\t\tType:     \"step_log\",\n   709→\t\t\tStepName: req.StepName,\n   710→\t\t\tMessage:  string(data),\n   711→\t\t})\n   712→\t}\n   713→\n   714→\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"no log files found matching filter\")\n   715→}\n   716→\n   717→// streamLiveLogs subscribes to the broadcaster and streams log lines in real\n   718→// time for an active run. The stream closes when the run completes or the\n   719→// client disconnects.\n   720→func (s *ClocheServer) streamLiveLogs(runID string, stream rpcgrpc.ServerStreamingServer[pb.LogEntry]) error {\n   721→\tsub := s.logBroadcast.Subscribe(runID)\n   722→\tdefer s.logBroadcast.Unsubscribe(runID, sub)\n   723→\n   724→\tctx := stream.Context()\n   725→\tfor {\n   726→\t\tselect {\n   727→\t\tcase <-ctx.Done():\n   728→\t\t\treturn ctx.Err()\n   729→\t\tcase line, ok := <-sub.C:\n   730→\t\t\tif !ok {\n   731→\t\t\t\t// Run completed — send terminal entry.\n   732→\t\t\t\trun, err := s.store.GetRun(context.Background(), runID)\n   733→\t\t\t\tif err == nil && run.State != domain.RunStateRunning && run.State != domain.RunStatePending {\n   734→\t\t\t\t\t_ = stream.Send(&pb.LogEntry{\n   735→\t\t\t\t\t\tType:      \"run_completed\",\n   736→\t\t\t\t\t\tResult:    string(run.State),\n   737→\t\t\t\t\t\tTimestamp: run.CompletedAt.String(),\n   738→\t\t\t\t\t\tMessage:   run.ErrorMessage,\n   739→\t\t\t\t\t})\n   740→\t\t\t\t}\n   741→\t\t\t\treturn nil\n   742→\t\t\t}\n   743→\t\t\tif err := stream.Send(&pb.LogEntry{\n   744→\t\t\t\tType:      \"log\",\n   745→\t\t\t\tStepName:  line.StepName,\n   746→\t\t\t\tMessage:   line.Content,\n   747→\t\t\t\tTimestamp: line.Timestamp,\n   748→\t\t\t}); err != nil {\n   749→\t\t\t\treturn err\n   750→\t\t\t}\n   751→\t\t}\n   752→\t}\n   753→}\n   754→\n   755→func (s *ClocheServer) StopRun(ctx context.Context, req *pb.StopRunRequest) (*pb.StopRunResponse, error) {\n   756→\ts.mu.Lock()\n   757→\tcontainerID, ok := s.runIDs[req.RunId]\n   758→\ts.mu.Unlock()\n   759→\n   760→\tif !ok {\n   761→\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"run %q not found or already completed\", req.RunId)\n   762→\t}\n   763→\n   764→\tif err := s.container.Stop(ctx, containerID); err != nil {\n   765→\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"stopping run: %w\", err)\n   766→\t}\n   767→\n   768→\t// Mark as cancelled in store\n   769→\trun, err := s.store.GetRun(ctx, req.RunId)\n   770→\tif err == nil {\n   771→\t\trun.Complete(domain.RunStateCancelled)\n   772→\t\t_ = s.store.UpdateRun(ctx, run)\n   773→\t}\n   774→\n   775→\treturn &pb.StopRunResponse{}, nil\n   776→}\n   777→\n   778→func (s *ClocheServer) DeleteContainer(ctx context.Context, req *pb.DeleteContainerRequest) (*pb.DeleteContainerResponse, error) {\n   779→\tif s.container == nil {\n   780→\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"no container runtime configured\")\n   781→\t}\n   782→\n   783→\tid := req.Id\n   784→\tif id == \"\" {\n   785→\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"id is required\")\n   786→\t}\n   787→\n   788→\t// Try to resolve as a run ID first\n   789→\tcontainerID := id\n   790→\trun, err := s.store.GetRun(ctx, id)\n   791→\tif err == nil {\n   792→\t\t// It's a run ID — use the container ID from the run record\n   793→\t\tif run.ContainerID == \"\" {\n   794→\t\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"run %q has no associated container\", id)\n   795→\t\t}\n   796→\t\tcontainerID = run.ContainerID\n   797→\t}\n   798→\n   799→\t// Remove the container\n   800→\tif err := s.container.Remove(ctx, containerID); err != nil {\n   801→\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"removing container: %w\", err)\n   802→\t}\n   803→\n   804→\t// If we resolved a run, clear the container_kept flag\n   805→\tif run != nil {\n   806→\t\trun.ContainerKept = false\n   807→\t\t_ = s.store.UpdateRun(ctx, run)\n   808→\t}\n   809→\n   810→\treturn &pb.DeleteContainerResponse{}, nil\n   811→}\n   812→\n   813→func (s *ClocheServer) EnableLoop(ctx context.Context, req *pb.EnableLoopRequest) (*pb.EnableLoopResponse, error) {\n   814→\tprojectDir := req.ProjectDir\n   815→\tif projectDir == \"\" {\n   816→\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"project_dir is required\")\n   817→\t}\n   818→\n   819→\t// Verify host.cloche exists\n   820→\thostPath := filepath.Join(projectDir, \".cloche\", \"host.cloche\")\n   821→\tif _, err := os.Stat(hostPath); err != nil {\n   822→\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"host.cloche not found in %s: %w\", projectDir, err)\n   823→\t}\n   824→\n   825→\t// Load project config for defaults.\n   826→\tprojCfg, _ := config.Load(projectDir)\n   827→\n   828→\tmaxConc := int(req.MaxConcurrent)\n   829→\tif maxConc <= 0 {\n   830→\t\tmaxConc = projCfg.Orchestration.Concurrency\n   831→\t}\n   832→\tif maxConc <= 0 {\n   833→\t\tmaxConc = 1\n   834→\t}\n   835→\n   836→\tstagger := time.Duration(float64(time.Second) * projCfg.Orchestration.StaggerSeconds)\n   837→\n   838→\t// Compute dedup timeout from config (default 5 minutes).\n   839→\tdedupTimeout := time.Duration(float64(time.Second) * projCfg.Orchestration.DedupSeconds)\n   840→\n   841→\tloopCfg := host.LoopConfig{\n   842→\t\tProjectDir:    projectDir,\n   843→\t\tMaxConcurrent: maxConc,\n   844→\t\tStaggerDelay:  stagger,\n   845→\t\tDedupTimeout:  dedupTimeout,\n   846→\t}\n   847→\n   848→\ts.mu.Lock()\n   849→\tdefer s.mu.Unlock()\n   850→\n   851→\t// Stop existing loop if running.\n   852→\tif existing, ok := s.loops[projectDir]; ok {\n   853→\t\texisting.Stop()\n   854→\t}\n   855→\n   856→\t// Check if host.cloche defines a list-tasks workflow for three-phase mode.\n   857→\tvar loop *host.Loop\n   858→\tif s.hasWorkflow(hostPath, \"list-tasks\") {\n   859→\t\tloop = s.createPhaseLoop(loopCfg, projectDir, hostPath, dedupTimeout)\n   860→\t} else {\n   861→\t\tloop = s.createLegacyLoop(loopCfg, projectDir, projCfg, dedupTimeout)\n   862→\t}\n   863→\n   864→\ts.loops[projectDir] = loop\n   865→\tloop.Start()\n   866→\n   867→\treturn &pb.EnableLoopResponse{}, nil\n   868→}\n   869→\n   870→// hasWorkflow checks if host.cloche contains a workflow with the given name.\n   871→func (s *ClocheServer) hasWorkflow(hostPath, workflowName string) bool {\n   872→\tdata, err := os.ReadFile(hostPath)\n   873→\tif err != nil {\n   874→\t\treturn false\n   875→\t}\n   876→\treturn strings.Contains(string(data), fmt.Sprintf(\"workflow %q\", workflowName))\n   877→}\n   878→\n   879→// createPhaseLoop creates a three-phase orchestration loop using list-tasks,\n   880→// main, and finalize workflows from host.cloche.\n   881→func (s *ClocheServer) createPhaseLoop(loopCfg host.LoopConfig, projectDir, hostPath string, dedupTimeout time.Duration) *host.Loop {\n   882→\t// Phase 1: list-tasks function\n   883→\tlistTasksFn := func(ctx context.Context, projDir string) ([]host.Task, error) {\n   884→\t\trunner := &host.Runner{\n   885→\t\t\tDispatcher: s,\n   886→\t\t\tStore:      s.store,\n   887→\t\t}\n   888→\t\ttasks, _, err := host.RunListTasksWorkflow(ctx, runner, projDir)\n   889→\t\treturn tasks, err\n   890→\t}\n   891→\n   892→\t// Phase 2: main function\n   893→\tmainFn := func(ctx context.Context, projDir string, taskID string) (*host.RunResult, error) {\n   894→\t\trunner := &host.Runner{\n   895→\t\t\tDispatcher:   s,\n   896→\t\t\tStore:        s.store,\n   897→\t\t\tCaptures:     s.captures,\n   898→\t\t\tLogBroadcast: s.logBroadcast,\n   899→\t\t\tTaskID:       taskID,\n   900→\t\t}\n   901→\t\treturn runner.RunNamed(ctx, projDir, \"main\")\n   902→\t}\n   903→\n   904→\t// Phase 3: finalize function (optional — only if host.cloche has it)\n   905→\tvar finalizeFn host.FinalizeFunc\n   906→\tif s.hasWorkflow(hostPath, \"finalize\") {\n   907→\t\tfinalizeFn = func(ctx context.Context, projDir string, taskID string, mainResult *host.RunResult) (*host.RunResult, error) {\n   908→\t\t\tmainRunID := \"\"\n   909→\t\t\tmainOutcome := \"failed\"\n   910→\t\t\tif mainResult != nil {\n   911→\t\t\t\tmainRunID = mainResult.RunID\n   912→\t\t\t\tmainOutcome = string(mainResult.State)\n   913→\t\t\t}\n   914→\t\t\trunner := &host.Runner{\n   915→\t\t\t\tDispatcher:   s,\n   916→\t\t\t\tStore:        s.store,\n   917→\t\t\t\tCaptures:     s.captures,\n   918→\t\t\t\tLogBroadcast: s.logBroadcast,\n   919→\t\t\t\tTaskID:       taskID,\n   920→\t\t\t\tExtraEnv: []string{\n   921→\t\t\t\t\t\"CLOCHE_MAIN_RUN_ID=\" + mainRunID,\n   922→\t\t\t\t\t\"CLOCHE_MAIN_OUTCOME=\" + mainOutcome,\n   923→\t\t\t\t},\n   924→\t\t\t}\n   925→\t\t\treturn runner.RunNamed(ctx, projDir, \"finalize\")\n   926→\t\t}\n   927→\t}\n   928→\n   929→\tlog.Printf(\"orchestration loop: three-phase mode enabled for %s (list-tasks + main + finalize, dedup=%s)\", projectDir, dedupTimeout)\n   930→\treturn host.NewPhaseLoop(loopCfg, s.store, listTasksFn, mainFn, finalizeFn)\n   931→}\n   932→\n   933→// createLegacyLoop creates a legacy single-function orchestration loop.\n   934→func (s *ClocheServer) createLegacyLoop(loopCfg host.LoopConfig, projectDir string, projCfg *config.Config, dedupTimeout time.Duration) *host.Loop {\n   935→\trunFn := func(ctx context.Context, projDir string, taskID string) (*host.RunResult, error) {\n   936→\t\trunner := &host.Runner{\n   937→\t\t\tDispatcher:   s,\n   938→\t\t\tStore:        s.store,\n   939→\t\t\tCaptures:     s.captures,\n   940→\t\t\tLogBroadcast: s.logBroadcast,\n   941→\t\t\tTaskID:       taskID,\n   942→\t\t}\n   943→\t\treturn runner.Run(ctx, projDir)\n   944→\t}\n   945→\n   946→\tloop := host.NewLoop(loopCfg, s.store, runFn)\n   947→\n   948→\t// Configure daemon-managed task assignment if a list-tasks command is set.\n   949→\tif cmd := projCfg.Orchestration.ListTasksCommand; cmd != \"\" {\n   950→\t\tloop.SetTaskAssigner(&host.ScriptTaskAssigner{Command: cmd})\n   951→\t\tlog.Printf(\"orchestration loop: task assignment enabled for %s (command=%q, dedup=%s)\", projectDir, cmd, dedupTimeout)\n   952→\t}\n   953→\n   954→\treturn loop\n   955→}\n   956→\n   957→// GetLoopTasks returns the current task pipeline state for a project's\n   958→// orchestration loop, formatted as web.TaskEntry values. Returns nil if no\n   959→// loop is active for the project.\n   960→func (s *ClocheServer) GetLoopTasks(projectDir string) []web.TaskEntry {\n   961→\ts.mu.Lock()\n   962→\tloop, ok := s.loops[projectDir]\n   963→\ts.mu.Unlock()\n   964→\tif !ok {\n   965→\t\treturn nil\n   966→\t}\n   967→\tsnapshot := loop.GetTaskSnapshot()\n   968→\tentries := make([]web.TaskEntry, len(snapshot))\n   969→\tfor i, e := range snapshot {\n   970→\t\tentry := web.TaskEntry{\n   971→\t\t\tID:          e.Task.ID,\n   972→\t\t\tStatus:      e.Task.Status,\n   973→\t\t\tTitle:       e.Task.Title,\n   974→\t\t\tDescription: e.Task.Description,\n   975→\t\t\tMetadata:    e.Task.Metadata,\n   976→\t\t\tAssigned:    e.Assigned,\n   977→\t\t\tRunID:       e.RunID,\n   978→\t\t}\n   979→\t\tif !e.AssignedAt.IsZero() {\n   980→\t\t\tentry.AssignedAt = e.AssignedAt.Format(time.RFC3339)\n   981→\t\t}\n   982→\t\tentries[i] = entry\n   983→\t}\n   984→\treturn entries\n   985→}\n   986→\n   987→func (s *ClocheServer) DisableLoop(ctx context.Context, req *pb.DisableLoopRequest) (*pb.DisableLoopResponse, error) {\n   988→\tprojectDir := req.ProjectDir\n   989→\tif projectDir == \"\" {\n   990→\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"project_dir is required\")\n   991→\t}\n   992→\n   993→\ts.mu.Lock()\n   994→\tdefer s.mu.Unlock()\n   995→\n   996→\tif loop, ok := s.loops[projectDir]; ok {\n   997→\t\tloop.Stop()\n   998→\t\tdelete(s.loops, projectDir)\n   999→\t}\n  1000→\n  1001→\treturn &pb.DisableLoopResponse{}, nil\n  1002→}\n  1003→\n  1004→func (s *ClocheServer) Shutdown(ctx context.Context, req *pb.ShutdownRequest) (*pb.ShutdownResponse, error) {\n  1005→\t// Stop all orchestration loops.\n  1006→\ts.mu.Lock()\n  1007→\tfor _, loop := range s.loops {\n  1008→\t\tloop.Stop()\n  1009→\t}\n  1010→\ts.loops = make(map[string]*host.Loop)\n  1011→\ts.mu.Unlock()\n  1012→\n  1013→\tif s.shutdownFn == nil {\n  1014→\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"shutdown not configured\")\n  1015→\t}\n  1016→\tgo s.shutdownFn()\n  1017→\treturn &pb.ShutdownResponse{}, nil\n  1018→}\n  1019→\n  1020→// indexLogFiles scans the extracted output directory and creates log_files index entries.\n  1021→func (s *ClocheServer) indexLogFiles(ctx context.Context, runID, outputDir string) {\n  1022→\tentries, err := os.ReadDir(outputDir)\n  1023→\tif err != nil {\n  1024→\t\tlog.Printf(\"run %s: failed to read output dir for indexing: %v\", runID, err)\n  1025→\t\treturn\n  1026→\t}\n  1027→\n  1028→\tnow := time.Now()\n  1029→\tfor _, entry := range entries {\n  1030→\t\tif entry.IsDir() {\n  1031→\t\t\tcontinue\n  1032→\t\t}\n  1033→\t\tname := entry.Name()\n  1034→\t\tif !strings.HasSuffix(name, \".log\") {\n  1035→\t\t\tcontinue\n  1036→\t\t}\n  1037→\n  1038→\t\tvar fileType, stepName string\n  1039→\t\tbase := strings.TrimSuffix(name, \".log\")\n  1040→\n  1041→\t\tswitch {\n  1042→\t\tcase name == \"full.log\":\n  1043→\t\t\tfileType = \"full\"\n  1044→\t\tcase name == \"container.log\":\n  1045→\t\t\t// container.log is internal, not indexed as a user-facing log type\n  1046→\t\t\tcontinue\n  1047→\t\tcase strings.HasPrefix(name, \"llm-\"):\n  1048→\t\t\tfileType = \"llm\"\n  1049→\t\t\tstepName = strings.TrimPrefix(base, \"llm-\")\n  1050→\t\tdefault:\n  1051→\t\t\tfileType = \"script\"\n  1052→\t\t\tstepName = base\n  1053→\t\t}\n  1054→\n  1055→\t\tinfo, _ := entry.Info()\n  1056→\t\tvar fileSize int64\n  1057→\t\tif info != nil {\n  1058→\t\t\tfileSize = info.Size()\n  1059→\t\t}\n  1060→\n  1061→\t\tlogEntry := &ports.LogFileEntry{\n  1062→\t\t\tRunID:     runID,\n  1063→\t\t\tStepName:  stepName,\n  1064→\t\t\tFileType:  fileType,\n  1065→\t\t\tFilePath:  filepath.Join(outputDir, name),\n  1066→\t\t\tFileSize:  fileSize,\n  1067→\t\t\tCreatedAt: now,\n  1068→\t\t}\n  1069→\t\tif err := s.logStore.SaveLogFile(ctx, logEntry); err != nil {\n  1070→\t\t\tlog.Printf(\"run %s: failed to index log file %s: %v\", runID, name, err)\n  1071→\t\t}\n  1072→\t}\n  1073→}\n  1074→\n  1075→func gitHEAD(dir string) string {\n  1076→\tcmd := exec.Command(\"git\", \"rev-parse\", \"HEAD\")\n  1077→\tcmd.Dir = dir\n  1078→\tout, err := cmd.Output()\n  1079→\tif err != nil {\n  1080→\t\treturn \"\"\n  1081→\t}\n  1082→\treturn strings.TrimSpace(string(out))\n  1083→}\n  1084→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01HqGxcttN3K6oLdYWbW3TM7","session_id":"4d7e8ba7-70ae-45e4-b438-c668f354765a","uuid":"1d61239c-5cdf-4517-a7d2-ee9a6a486dbe"}
