[2026-03-13T18:28:28Z] [llm] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01JDqMpqRosYVGah9B6VJg4Y","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Subdirectory Layout, Daemon-Side Extraction, and Poll Command\n     2→\n     3→**Date:** 2026-03-01\n     4→\n     5→## Overview\n     6→\n     7→Three related changes to Cloche:\n     8→\n     9→1. Move cloche project files into a `./cloche/` subdirectory of the host project, separating host-level files (CLAUDE.md, .git, build config) from agent-level files.\n    10→2. Replace the in-container git push mechanism with daemon-side result extraction using `docker cp` and host-side git operations (with worktrees for concurrency).\n    11→3. Add a `poll` command that blocks until a run reaches a terminal state or its container has been dead for >1 minute.\n    12→\n    13→## 1. Directory Layout\n    14→\n    15→### Host project (user's repo root)\n    16→\n    17→```\n    18→my-project/\n    19→├── .git/\n    20→├── .gitignore\n    21→├── .gitworktrees/         # Daemon-managed git worktrees (gitignored)\n    22→├── CLAUDE.md              # Host-level agent instructions\n    23→├── README.md\n    24→├── cloche/                # Everything cloche manages\n    25→│   ├── develop.cloche     # Workflow DSL file(s)\n    26→│   ├── Dockerfile\n    27→│   ├── CLAUDE.md          # Inner agent instructions\n    28→│   ├── .cloche/\n    29→│   │   ├── config\n    30→│   │   ├── prompts/\n    31→│   │   │   ├── implement.md\n    32→│   │   │   └── fix.md\n    33→│   │   ├── <run-id>/      # Per-run output (gitignored)\n    34→│   │   │   ├── prompt.txt\n    35→│   │   │   └── output/\n    36→│   │   └── ...\n    37→│   └── <source files>     # Project code the agent works on\n    38→└── <host-level files>\n    39→```\n    40→\n    41→### Inside the container\n    42→\n    43→```\n    44→/workspace/                # = contents of host's ./cloche/\n    45→├── develop.cloche\n    46→├── Dockerfile\n    47→├── CLAUDE.md\n    48→├── .cloche/\n    49→│   ├── config\n    50→│   ├── prompts/\n    51→│   └── ...\n    52→└── <source files>\n    53→```\n    54→\n    55→The container sees a flat `/workspace/` — the contents of `./cloche/` are copied directly, not nested.\n    56→\n    57→### Gitignore additions\n    58→\n    59→`cloche init` adds to the host `.gitignore`:\n    60→\n    61→```\n    62→cloche/.cloche/*/\n    63→.gitworktrees/\n    64→```\n    65→\n    66→This ignores per-run output directories and worktrees, but keeps `cloche/.cloche/config` and `cloche/.cloche/prompts/` tracked.\n    67→\n    68→## 2. Container Lifecycle and Result Extraction\n    69→\n    70→### Run start\n    71→\n    72→1. The daemon records `base_sha` = current HEAD of the host repo.\n    73→2. `base_sha` is stored in the run record (new column in SQLite `runs` table).\n    74→3. `docker cp <host>/cloche/. <container>:/workspace/`\n    75→4. Container starts; agent runs the workflow autonomously.\n    76→\n    77→### Run completion\n    78→\n    79→When the container exits (success or failure):\n    80→\n    81→1. **Copy out:** `docker cp <container>:/workspace/. <tempdir>/`\n    82→2. **Create worktree:** `git worktree add --detach <project>/.gitworktrees/cloche/<run-id> <base_sha>`\n    83→3. **Populate:** Copy `<tempdir>` contents into `<worktree>/cloche/`\n    84→4. **Commit:**\n    85→   - `git checkout -b cloche/<run-id>` (in the worktree)\n    86→   - `git add cloche/`\n    87→   - `git commit -m \"cloche run <run-id>: <workflow-name> (<result>)\"`\n    88→5. **Cleanup:**\n    89→   - `git worktree remove <worktree-dir>`\n    90→   - Remove temp dir\n    91→   - Remove container (unless `--keep-container`)\n    92→\n    93→### Concurrency\n    94→\n    95→Each extraction uses its own git worktree at `<project>/.gitworktrees/cloche/<run-id>/`. Multiple extractions can run concurrently with no locking.\n    96→\n    97→### Error handling\n    98→\n    99→- If the container crashes, still attempt `docker cp` (the container filesystem persists until `docker rm`).\n   100→- If git operations fail, log the error, keep the container for debugging, and don't delete the temp dir.\n   101→\n   102→## 3. Poll Command\n   103→\n   104→### Usage\n   105→\n   106→```\n   107→cloche poll <run-id>\n   108→```\n   109→\n   110→### Behavior\n   111→\n   112→1. Connects to daemon via gRPC.\n   113→2. Polls `GetStatus(<run-id>)` every 2 seconds.\n   114→3. Prints status changes as they happen:\n   115→\n   116→```\n   117→[12:03:45] Run abc123 is running\n   118→[12:03:45] Step \"implement\" started\n   119→[12:04:12] Step \"implement\" completed: success\n   120→[12:04:12] Step \"test\" started\n   121→[12:04:30] Step \"test\" completed: fail\n   122→[12:04:30] Step \"fix\" started\n   123→[12:05:01] Step \"fix\" completed: success\n   124→[12:05:01] Step \"test\" started (retry)\n   125→[12:05:15] Step \"test\" completed: success\n   126→[12:05:15] Run abc123 succeeded\n   127→```\n   128→\n   129→4. Exits when:\n   130→   - The run reaches a terminal state (succeeded, failed, cancelled), **or**\n   131→   - The associated container has been dead (or never started) for >1 minute.\n   132→\n   133→### Exit codes\n   134→\n   135→- `0` — run succeeded\n   136→- `1` — everything else (failed, cancelled, container dead)\n   137→\n   138→### Protocol changes\n   139→\n   140→Add to the `GetStatusResponse` proto:\n   141→- `bool container_alive` — whether the Docker container is currently running\n   142→- `google.protobuf.Timestamp container_dead_since` — when the container was last seen alive (if dead)\n   143→\n   144→The daemon checks Docker container state when responding to status requests.\n   145→\n   146→## 4. Changes to `cloche init`\n   147→\n   148→`cloche init` now scaffolds into `./cloche/`:\n   149→\n   150→1. Creates `./cloche/` directory."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_014nB1uYcqdGQDnmCdayJAtm","session_id":"4d7e8ba7-70ae-45e4-b438-c668f354765a","uuid":"b5d4215a-9fc3-4916-895c-35a3c4c79eb7"}
