[2026-03-13T18:28:28Z] [llm] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01HqGxcttN3K6oLdYWbW3TM7","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information I need. Let me compile a comprehensive report.\n\n## Summary: `cloche list` Command State and Filter Flags\n\nI've conducted a thorough investigation of the codebase. Here's what I found:\n\n### Current Implementation Status\n\nThe `cloche list` command **is fully implemented** with all filter flags you mentioned. Here's the complete breakdown:\n\n---\n\n### 1. CLI Command Implementation\n**File**: `/workspace/cmd/cloche/main.go` (lines 242-330)\n\nThe `cmdList` function implements the list subcommand with the following flags:\n\n- **`--all`** - Show runs from all projects (default: current project only)\n- **`--project, -p DIR`** - Filter by project directory\n- **`--state, -s STATE`** - Filter by run state (pending, running, succeeded, failed, cancelled)\n- **`--limit, -n NUM`** - Limit the number of results returned\n- **`--issue, -i ID`** - Filter by issue/task ID (maps to `task_id` internally)\n\nDefault behavior: When no project filter and not `--all`, defaults to current working directory.\n\n### 2. Help Documentation\n**File**: `/workspace/cmd/cloche/help.go` (lines 158-185)\n\nComplete help text for the list command is present:\n```\ncloche list — List workflow runs\n\nShows all runs for the current project, or all runs across all projects\nwith --all. Results can be filtered by state, project, issue, or limited\nto a fixed number.\n\nUsage:\n  cloche list [flags]\n\nFlags:\n  --all              Show runs from all projects (default: current project only).\n  --project, -p DIR  Filter by project directory.\n  --state, -s STATE  Filter by run state (pending, running, succeeded, failed, cancelled).\n  --limit, -n NUM    Limit the number of results returned.\n  --issue, -i ID     Filter by issue/task ID.\n```\n\n### 3. Proto Definition\n**File**: `/workspace/api/proto/cloche/v1/cloche.proto` (lines 90-112)\n\nThe RPC service defines:\n- `ListRunsRequest` (lines 90-96) with fields:\n  - `bool all`\n  - `string project_dir`\n  - `string state`\n  - `int32 limit`\n  - `string task_id`\n- `ListRunsResponse` (lines 98-100) with `repeated RunSummary runs`\n- `RunSummary` (lines 102-112) containing run metadata\n\n### 4. Domain Model\n**File**: `/workspace/internal/domain/run.go` (lines 18-25)\n\nThe `RunListFilter` struct defines the filter structure:\n```go\ntype RunListFilter struct {\n\tProjectDir string\n\tState      RunState\n\tTaskID     string\n\tLimit      int\n\tSince      time.Time\n}\n```\n\n### 5. Store Interface\n**File**: `/workspace/internal/ports/store.go` (lines 10-19)\n\nThe `RunStore` interface defines:\n- `ListRunsFiltered(ctx context.Context, filter domain.RunListFilter) ([]*domain.Run, error)`\n\n### 6. SQLite Implementation\n**File**: `/workspace/internal/adapters/sqlite/store.go` (lines 244-277)\n\nThe `ListRunsFiltered` method implements filtering with:\n- Project directory filter (WHERE clause)\n- State filter (WHERE clause)\n- TaskID filter (WHERE clause, maps to `task_id` column)\n- Time-based filter (`Since`) - supports filtering by started_at timestamp\n- Limit support (SQL LIMIT clause)\n- Ordering: running state prioritized first, then by started_at DESC\n\nDatabase schema includes all necessary fields:\n- `project_dir` (line 74)\n- `state` (line 51)\n- `task_id` (line 85)\n- `started_at` (line 53)\n\n### 7. gRPC Server Implementation\n**File**: `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go` (lines 387-420)\n\nThe `ListRuns` RPC handler:\n- Converts proto request to domain `RunListFilter` (lines 388-393)\n- Implements default behavior: when no project filter and not `--all`, defaults to last 1 hour (lines 395-398)\n- Calls `store.ListRunsFiltered(ctx, filter)` (line 400)\n- Transforms results to proto `RunSummary` messages (lines 405-419)\n\n---\n\n### Output Format\nThe CLI displays runs in a columnar format (line 310 in main.go):\n```\n{run_id}  {workflow_name}  {state}  {type}  [title]  [container_id]  [error_message]\n```\n\n---\n\n### Key Files to Reference\n1. `/workspace/cmd/cloche/main.go` - CLI argument parsing and RPC calls\n2. `/workspace/cmd/cloche/help.go` - Help text documentation\n3. `/workspace/api/proto/cloche/v1/cloche.proto` - RPC definitions\n4. `/workspace/internal/domain/run.go` - Filter struct definition\n5. `/workspace/internal/ports/store.go` - Store interface\n6. `/workspace/internal/adapters/sqlite/store.go` - SQLite query implementation (ListRunsFiltered)\n7. `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go` - RPC handler (ListRuns method)\n\nAll filter flags are fully implemented and functional, with complete database query support."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: ad1c0158aad297203 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 56334\ntool_uses: 11\nduration_ms: 19844</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4d7e8ba7-70ae-45e4-b438-c668f354765a","uuid":"35558150-d438-44a3-8866-091af3a18279","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"I need to understand the current state of the `cloche list` command and any filter flags (--project, --state, --limit, --issue) that have been added. Please:\n\n1. Search for any \"list\" subcommand implementation in cmd/cloche/ \n2. Search for ListRuns or similar RPC/store methods related to listing runs\n3. Check the proto file at api/proto/cloche/v1/cloche.proto for ListRuns request/response\n4. Check internal/ports/store.go for any list/filter interfaces\n5. Check internal/adapters/sqlite/store.go for list implementation\n6. Check internal/adapters/grpc/server.go for list implementation\n7. Check cmd/cloche/main.go and cmd/cloche/help.go for list command and flags\n\nBe very thorough - read all relevant files completely.","agentId":"ad1c0158aad297203","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information I need.