[2026-03-13T18:28:28Z] [llm] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01GkFczUUGiKuNd9x7G3e2uz","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Project Pages Design\n     2→\n     3→**Date:** 2026-03-06\n     4→**Status:** Design\n     5→\n     6→## Problem\n     7→\n     8→The projects landing page shows only health dots and a \"View Runs\" link. There is no\n     9→dedicated project page. Useful project-level information and controls are either missing\n    10→or buried in other views.\n    11→\n    12→## Goal\n    13→\n    14→Add a dedicated `/projects/{name}` page with four panels:\n    15→\n    16→1. **Orchestrator control** — view status, enable/disable the auto-poll loop, override concurrency\n    17→2. **Project info** — Docker image, prompt file evolution history, project version\n    18→3. **Tasks** — live task pipeline view showing discovered tasks, their status, and assigned runs\n    19→4. **Workflow view** — read-only DAG of steps/wires, drillable to prompt/script content\n    20→\n    21→## Route\n    22→\n    23→```\n    24→GET /projects/{name}\n    25→```\n    26→\n    27→`{name}` is the project label (same string used in `/api/projects/{name}/trigger`).\n    28→The handler resolves the label back to a project directory via `projectLabels()`.\n    29→\n    30→Project cards on the landing page link to `/projects/{name}`. The project page\n    31→includes a compact recent-runs strip (last 10 dots) and a \"View all runs\" link to\n    32→`/projects/{name}/runs` for the filtered runs list.\n    33→\n    34→## Panel 1: Orchestrator Control\n    35→\n    36→### Display\n    37→- Status line: `Enabled / Disabled`, in-flight run count, concurrency limit\n    38→- Toggle button: **Enable** / **Disable** (controls the auto-poll loop for this project)\n    39→- Concurrency override: number input + **Apply** button (runtime only, resets on daemon restart)\n    40→\n    41→### API additions\n    42→\n    43→```\n    44→GET  /api/projects/{name}/orchestrator\n    45→POST /api/projects/{name}/orchestrator/start\n    46→POST /api/projects/{name}/orchestrator/stop\n    47→POST /api/projects/{name}/orchestrator/concurrency   body: {\"concurrency\": N}\n    48→```\n    49→\n    50→`GET` response:\n    51→```json\n    52→{\n    53→  \"enabled\": true,\n    54→  \"in_flight\": 1,\n    55→  \"concurrency\": 2\n    56→}\n    57→```\n    58→\n    59→The orchestrator currently has no per-project enable/disable concept. We add an\n    60→`enabled` flag to `ProjectConfig` (default true when registered). Start/stop toggle\n    61→this flag. When disabled, `Run()` returns 0 without dispatching.\n    62→\n    63→Concurrency override updates `ProjectConfig.Concurrency` in memory only.\n    64→\n    65→The Handler needs a reference to the `*orchestrator.Orchestrator` (or a minimal\n    66→interface exposing `Status(dir)`, `SetEnabled(dir, bool)`, `SetConcurrency(dir, int)`,\n    67→`InFlight(dir)`). Wire this in via a `HandlerOption`.\n    68→\n    69→## Panel 2: Project Info\n    70→\n    71→### Display\n    72→- **Docker image**: read the `FROM` line(s) from `.cloche/Dockerfile`. Show the last\n    73→  non-builder stage's base image (i.e. the stage that produces the final image).\n    74→- **Project version**: integer, sourced from `.cloche/version` (see Project Versioning\n    75→  design). Display as `v3`.\n    76→- **Prompt files**: for each file under `.cloche/prompts/`, show:\n    77→  - Current file contents in a collapsible accordion\n    78→  - Git commit history (short SHA, date, message)\n    79→  - Click a commit entry to expand and show a unified diff inline\n    80→\n    81→### API additions\n    82→\n    83→```\n    84→GET /api/projects/{name}/info\n    85→```\n    86→\n    87→Response:\n    88→```json\n    89→{\n    90→  \"docker_image\": \"ubuntu:24.04\",\n    91→  \"version\": 3,\n    92→  \"prompt_files\": [\n    93→    {\n    94→      \"path\": \".cloche/prompts/implement.md\",\n    95→      \"content\": \"Full text of the prompt file...\",\n    96→      \"history\": [\n    97→        {\"sha\": \"abc1234\", \"date\": \"2026-03-05\", \"message\": \"evolution: tighten scope\"},\n    98→        {\"sha\": \"def5678\", \"date\": \"2026-03-01\", \"message\": \"init\"}\n    99→      ]\n   100→    }\n   101→  ]\n   102→}\n   103→```\n   104→\n   105→Implementation: run `git log --follow --oneline -- <file>` in the project directory\n   106→via `exec.Command`. Diff for a specific commit loaded lazily on click via:\n   107→\n   108→```\n   109→GET /api/projects/{name}/info/prompt-diff?file=.cloche/prompts/implement.md&sha=abc1234\n   110→```\n   111→\n   112→Returns plain text unified diff (`git show <sha> -- <file>`).\n   113→\n   114→## Panel 3: Tasks\n   115→\n   116→### Display\n   117→- Table showing discovered tasks: Task ID, Title, Status, Assigned (yes/no), Run link\n   118→- Status badges: `open` (running style), `closed` (succeeded style), other (pending style)\n   119→- Auto-refreshes every 5 seconds via polling\n   120→- Shows \"No tasks discovered\" when the project has no list-tasks output\n   121→\n   122→### API\n   123→\n   124→```\n   125→GET /api/projects/{name}/tasks\n   126→```\n   127→\n   128→Returns the task pipeline state for the project's orchestration loop.\n   129→\n   130→### Runs page changes\n   131→\n   132→- `list-tasks` workflow runs are hidden from the Runs page (both server-rendered and\n   133→  JS-rendered views)\n   134→- Runs with the same `task_id` are grouped under a task header row\n   135→- The task header shows an aggregate status badge (active statuses running/pending outweigh terminal ones; among terminal-only runs the most recently started determines the result)\n   136→- The `task_id` and `task_status` fields are included in the `/api/runs` JSON response\n   137→- Runs without a `task_id` appear ungrouped below task groups\n   138→\n   139→## Panel 4: Workflow View\n   140→\n   141→### Display\n   142→- Two-level tab navigation:\n   143→  - **Location tabs** (Container / Host) shown when both container and host workflows exist\n   144→  - **Workflow tabs** shown when the active location has multiple workflows\n   145→- Per workflow: a read-only DAG rendered client-side\n   146→  - Nodes = steps, rendered as boxes showing step name + type icon (agent 🤖 / script 📜 / workflow 🔁)\n   147→  - Edges = wires, labeled with the result name (e.g. `success`, `fail`)\n   148→  - Terminal nodes `done` and `abort` rendered distinctly\n   149→- Clicking a step node opens a right-side **drawer panel** (CSS slide-in):\n   150→  - Step name and type"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_014nB1uYcqdGQDnmCdayJAtm","session_id":"4d7e8ba7-70ae-45e4-b438-c668f354765a","uuid":"c3564db5-fc08-4d7e-b96e-aaa720483469"}
