[2026-03-13T18:28:28Z] [llm] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01CKYqsEEFkLEu8s8Va4cZVd","type":"tool_result","content":"   620→### `cloche status`\n   621→\n   622→```\n   623→cloche status <run-id>\n   624→```\n   625→\n   626→Shows run title, type (`host`/`container`), state, active steps, and per-step results.\n   627→\n   628→### `cloche list`\n   629→\n   630→```\n   631→cloche list [--all]\n   632→```\n   633→\n   634→Lists runs for the current project directory. Pass `--all` to show runs across all projects.\n   635→\n   636→### `cloche logs`\n   637→\n   638→```\n   639→cloche logs <run-id> [--step <name>] [--type <full|script|llm>] [-f]\n   640→```\n   641→\n   642→| Flag | Description |\n   643→|------|-------------|\n   644→| `--step <name>` | Show only logs for the specified step. |\n   645→| `--type <full\\|script\\|llm>` | Log type filter. |\n   646→| `-f` | Follow mode: display existing logs then continue streaming new lines as they arrive (like `tail -f`). |\n   647→\n   648→Without `-f`, displays all logs captured to date and exits (even for active runs). With `-f` on an active run, existing logs are sent first, then new output is streamed in real time via gRPC until the run completes.\n   649→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4d7e8ba7-70ae-45e4-b438-c668f354765a","uuid":"12fdd603-536c-4d4f-b0f6-e665d77f267f","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspace/docs/USAGE.md","content":"### `cloche status`\n\n```\ncloche status <run-id>\n```\n\nShows run title, type (`host`/`container`), state, active steps, and per-step results.\n\n### `cloche list`\n\n```\ncloche list [--all]\n```\n\nLists runs for the current project directory. Pass `--all` to show runs across all projects.\n\n### `cloche logs`\n\n```\ncloche logs <run-id> [--step <name>] [--type <full|script|llm>] [-f]\n```\n\n| Flag | Description |\n|------|-------------|\n| `--step <name>` | Show only logs for the specified step. |\n| `--type <full\\|script\\|llm>` | Log type filter. |\n| `-f` | Follow mode: display existing logs then continue streaming new lines as they arrive (like `tail -f`). |\n\nWithout `-f`, displays all logs captured to date and exits (even for active runs). With `-f` on an active run, existing logs are sent first, then new output is streamed in real time via gRPC until the run completes.\n","numLines":30,"startLine":620,"totalLines":828}}}
